        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4 leading-tight">Fire Extinguisher Inspection in Chula Vista, CA: What Every Business Owner Needs to Know</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">If you own or manage a commercial property in Chula Vista, CA, your fire extinguishers are a legal requirement with specific inspection schedules enforced by the Chula Vista Fire Department. Here's exactly what NFPA 10 and the California Fire Code (Title 19 CCR) require, what inspections cost, and how to avoid violations.</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3">Chula Vista Fire Extinguisher Requirements</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">The City of Chula Vista enforces the California Fire Code (Title 19 CCR), requiring all commercial properties to maintain portable fire extinguishers in compliance with <a href="/compliance/nfpa-10/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 10</a>. Chula Vista is San Diego County's second-largest city and one of the fastest-growing communities in Southern California. The commercial landscape spans the Otay Ranch Town Center and Millenia retail districts, the Otay Mesa industrial zone near the US-Mexico border crossing, and a dense concentration of restaurants and food service businesses. California mandates automatic fire sprinklers in most new commercial construction — but portable extinguisher compliance remains a mandatory annual obligation regardless of sprinkler system presence.</p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Monthly Visual Inspections</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Monthly visual inspections can be performed by trained building staff. Verify each unit is in place, unobstructed, pressure gauge reads in the operating range, tamper seal is intact, and pull pin is present. Document every check — absence of monthly records significantly increases liability exposure.</p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Annual Professional Inspections</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Annual inspections must be performed by a licensed technician. California requires fire extinguisher service contractors to hold an OSFM license from the California State Fire Marshal's Office. Verify licensing at osfm.fire.ca.gov before scheduling service. The technician inspects all components and attaches a dated service tag. Failed units must be immediately serviced, recharged, or replaced.</p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">6-Year Internal Examination & 12-Year Hydrostatic Testing</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Every six years, stored-pressure units must be internally examined for corrosion and agent degradation. At 12 years, cylinders must pass hydrostatic pressure testing — units that fail are condemned. Your service provider should track these intervals based on each unit's manufacture date.</p>
